+## [2026-07-10T00:00:00Z] tui — `[i]` info panel replaces the idea-preview strip
+
+**Action:** Repurposed the grid-mode `i` gesture from the bottom-strip idea-preview (`mode: :idea_preview`) to a read-only, full-screen **info panel** (`mode: :info`) and added `[i] info` to the bottom legend (`BubbleModel#footer_hint`). New `Hive::Tui::Views::InfoOverlay` renders a bordered box (mirrors `help_overlay`) with common fields — slug, stage, `created_at` + original idea text (parsed from `idea.md` frontmatter via the existing `idea_frontmatter` splitter), task-folder path, latest-log path (`LogTail::FileResolver.latest_in_dirs`) — plus a stage-specific section: raw `brainstorm.md` contents (2-brainstorm), `plan.md` (3-plan), or the tail of the latest execute log (4-execute); 1-inbox has no extra section. All data gathering lives in `BubbleModel#open_info_overlay` (side-effect path, like `OpenLogTail`/`OpenRedStatusDetail`); every disk read is resilient (missing idea.md / logs / stage file degrade to a placeholder, never a flash or crash). Close keys are `q` / `Esc` / `i`; every other key is an inert NOOP so the panel stays open (read-only, A7). No scrolling this iteration — overflow is truncated with `…`, clamped to `model.rows`/`cols`. The old `Views::IdeaPreview`, `Messages::OpenIdeaPreview`, `mode: :idea_preview`, and the `idea_preview_text`/`idea_preview_slug` model fields were removed; `Model::InfoOverlayState` replaces them. `footer_hint` now exceeds the 70-col budget (the required `[i] info` entry is unconditional), so `default_footer` truncates the tail on narrow terminals via `Views::Format.truncate` — the prior `test_default_footer_hint_omits_o_at_70_col_budget` regression test was replaced accordingly.
